Package: Covid19CasesPlot
Type: Package
Title: Plot COVID19 Patterns Using Data from John Hopkins University
Version: 1.0
Date: 2020-04-12
Author: Damiano Fantini
Maintainer: Damiano Fantini <damiano.fantini@gmail.com>
Description: Retrieve latest COVID-19 data provided by John Hopkins University (Baltimore, US) and visualize the trend of new cases and deaths due to COVID-19 infection in a country or US state of interest. Points indicate the number of new cases or deaths measured day by day. Trendlines are computed by LOESS.
License: GPL-2
Depends: R (>= 3.5)
Imports: stats, ggplot2, utils, reshape2
Suggests: dplyr, gridExtra, devtools, rmarkdown, knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr  
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
URL: https://www.data-pulse.com/dev_site/covid19/
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
